Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of generalized low-density parity-check (GLDPC) codes for 5G Ultra Reliable Communication (URC), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes the message passing process and complexity of the GLDPC code, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the GLDPC codes with respect to other state-of-the-art code and decoder designs, which is related to computer science and networking (cs.CC).
